title: Appointments to Hospital Authority
content_text:
p>
          The Government announced today (March 28) the re-appointment of three 
          serving members and the appointment of three new members to the 
          Hospital Authority, with effect from April 1, 2013. Ms Chiang Lai-yuen, Mr Pang Yiu-kai and Professor Maurice Yap Keng-hung 
          are re-appointed for two years. The new members are Professor Chan Ka-leung, Dr Kam Pok-man and 
          Professor Raymond Liang Hin-suen. Professor Chan is appointed for one

Professor Raymond Liang Hin-suen. Professor Chan is appointed for one 
          year, and Dr Kam and Professor Liang for two years. Following is a brief biography of the new members: Professor Chan Ka-leung is the Interim Dean of the Faculty of Medicine 
          of the Chinese University of Hong Kong. He is currently a member of 
          the Steering Committee on Strategic Review on Healthcare Manpower 
          Planning and Professional Development. Dr Kam Pok-man is a certified public accountant. He is currently Chief 
          Executive Officer of the Financial Reporting Council. He is also an

Executive Officer of the Financial Reporting Council. He is also an 
          Adjunct Associate Professor in the School of Accountancy of the 
          Chinese University of Hong Kong and an Adjunct Professor in the 
          Department of Accountancy at City University of Hong Kong. Professor Raymond Liang Hin-suen is Chair Professor of Haematology and 
          Oncology at the University of Hong Kong, and was the Immediate Past 
          President of the Hong Kong Academy of Medicine. He is now serving as a 
          member of the Steering Committee on Strategic Review on Healthcare

member of the Steering Committee on Strategic Review on Healthcare 
          Manpower Planning and Professional Development. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, welcomed the new 
          members to the Authority. He also thanked Professor Fok Tai-fai, who 
          has retired from the Hospital Authority with effect from January 1, 
          2013, as well as Mr Lawrence Lee Kam-hung and Mr David Lie-A-Cheong 
          Tai-chong, who will retire with effect from April 1, 2013, for their

advice and contribution to the Hospital Authority over the years. The Hospital Authority, as from April 1, 2013, will comprise a chairman, 23 non-official members, three public officers and one principal officer from the Hospital Authority. The new membership list is as follows: Chairman:
